# StyleUp Backend Standards

This is the single source of truth for all StyleUp backend work.

## Project Context

- NestJS backend serving a React Native (Expo) mobile app for a barber/beauty booking marketplace in Kerala, India.
- Stack: MongoDB/Mongoose, Redis, JWT auth, Razorpay payments.
- Payments are Razorpay UPI Intent only. UPI Collect is deprecated as of Feb 2026 and must not be scaffolded or referenced.
- Architecture: modular monolith using hexagonal/ports-adapters boundaries.

## Architecture

- Flow is `Controller -> Service -> Repository` (ports/adapters). Business logic never lives in controllers.
- One module per domain. No cross-module direct DB access; call the module's exported service.
- REST only. Do not introduce gRPC.
- DTOs are required for every request and response.
- Never expose Mongoose documents directly from controllers; map to response DTOs.
- Every new module ships with: module, controller, service, DTOs, schema if applicable, and barrel `index.ts`.

## Mobile API Contract

- Use the standard response envelope: `{ success, data, error?: { code, message } }`.
- Pagination is required on all list endpoints. Cursor-based pagination is preferred over offset.
- Error codes must be stable enum-like strings, for example `BOOKING_SLOT_TAKEN`. Never force the mobile client to parse raw error messages.
- All timestamps are ISO 8601 UTC. Timezone display is the client's job.
- GeoJSON coordinates are `[longitude, latitude]`, never `[latitude, longitude]`. Double-check this every time.
- Booking and availability sync endpoints must support `updatedAfter` or ETags/`If-Modified-Since`.
- Idempotency keys are required on booking creation and payment endpoints because mobile clients retry on flaky networks.
- Configure server-side request timeouts so slow queries never hang a mobile client.
- APIs are versioned from day one under `/api/v1`; mobile clients cannot force-update.

## Auth

- Login is OTP-based only. Do not add passwords.
- JWT pair: access token 15 minutes, refresh token 7 days, refresh rotation on use.
- Every token has a `jti` UUID v4.
- Redis blocklist entries are keyed by `jti`; TTL must match remaining token lifetime.
- Compose guards with `@UseGuards()` decorators. Never do manual auth or role checks inside controllers.
- Rate-limit OTP request endpoints per phone number via Redis.

## Payments

- Razorpay UPI Intent only. Never use or mention UPI Collect.
- Verify Razorpay webhook signatures before any processing.
- Payment state transitions go through an explicit state machine: `pending -> processing -> success | failed`.
- Never mutate booking status directly from a webhook.
- Store all amounts as integer paise. Never use floats.
- Do not touch payment state machine logic without explicit approval.

## Data Integrity

- Any geo-queried collection must define a `2dsphere` index.
- Design compound indexes around actual query patterns.
- Use soft deletes with `deletedAt` for bookings, users, and payment-linked records. Never hard delete them.
- Use Mongoose sessions/transactions for operations touching booking, payment, and provider availability together.
- Use optimistic locking or an explicit status-check guard for booking slot reservation to prevent double-booking races.

## Security

- Never log full phone numbers, OTPs, JWTs, or Razorpay payloads. Mask or redact logger output.
- Helmet plus rate limiting (per-IP and per-user) applies to all public endpoints, not only auth.
- Sanitize client-supplied query input against Mongoose operator injection (`$where`, `$gt`, etc.).
- Secrets are never hardcoded or committed. `.env` must stay gitignored.
- CORS whitelist must be explicit. Never use `origin: '*'`, including in development.

## Testing

- Unit tests are required for service-layer business logic.
- Minimum coverage focus: payment state transitions and booking conflict checks.
- E2E test for the full booking flow is required before the bookings module is considered done.
- Never skip tests silently. If a task would require skipping tests, flag it explicitly.

## Observability

- Use structured logging with request IDs correlated end-to-end.
- Maintain `/health` and `/health/detailed` endpoints. Detailed health includes DB and Redis latency.

## API Documentation

- Every DTO gets `@ApiProperty()` Swagger decorators.
- Swagger is the contract source of truth between this backend repo and the separate mobile app repo.

## Dev Tooling

- Provide a seed script for local dev with sample providers, services, and time slots so the DB does not need manual repopulation after every reset.

## Code Style

- Keep responses, comments, and PR descriptions concise and free of filler.
- TypeScript strict mode is required. No implicit `any`; do not use explicit `any`.
- Prefer composition over inheritance for services.

## Boundaries

- Do not add new npm packages without flagging them first.
- Do not change existing module or folder structure without explicit instruction.
- Do not touch payment state machine logic without explicit approval.
- Do not write feature or business logic when a task is scoped as setup or scaffolding only.
- Do not skip tests silently.

## Verification Habit

End every task with an explicit checklist specific to what was built. Include applicable items such as:

- Boots clean.
- Relevant endpoint manually verified.
- Lint and Prettier clean.
- Tests passing.
- No scope creep.
- No unapproved package additions.
- No feature/business logic added during setup/scaffolding work.
